snippet.textDisplay:
im really glad that one of the screen junkies' most controversial takes is calling make a man out of you a bathroom break. ha. commenters, you all have my respect. (btw i think it wasnt necessarily the song they were calling out, but more of the montage itself) but honestly i don't think it was just such a simple montage where you could skip it and not miss anything important. they show an actual scene where mulan is given an out and could potentially leave safely and go back home and pretend none of this happened but she takes one look at the obstacle none of them had been able to overcome and SHE's the only one who's there working her butt off to try and figure it out because she wants to prove to herself that she CAN do it that she can survive here. and mulan with her creative thinking that she's shown from literally the very start of the film (did yalls see that chicken feeding mechanism she made that was so simple yet ingenious?) was able to figure out how to use the weights that were dragging her down, to her advantage and they were what made her succeed in overcoming the obstacle. her being her, wanting to prove herself and her unique way of thinking. ALL of that was the crucial point and highlight of the montage. so sure, it could be broken down into she turns into a man at the end, but i'd argue there's more to the journey of that montage than meets the eye.

(ps im so glad yalls did the music, since yalls werent doing them lately (tangled), i think the last one was for the greatest showman?, i considered it a possibility plus you guys kept on saying in other stuff that there were only 2 songs in mulan but ahh im so glad yalls finally took note of the other ones. yalls have my respect for that)
